	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey.<br><br>If I'm entirely honest, I'm not entirely sure what you're asking about.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, using my incredible powers of deduction, I'm inclined to think you have just started a new necromancer* and are looking for the zone 'The Hole'**.<br><br><i>*took me 30minutes to find the necro guild<br>**Where is this &quot;hole&quot; you have to put the key in to fight with erudite necro?</i><br><br>The Hole, is a zone, accessed through Paineel.  (Which of course is where you will have started, as an Erudite necromancer.)  There is a lake with a boulder, which is the passageway to The Hole.  The boulder is bypassed via a key.  However, it's not a suitable place to hunt at low levels.  (The creatures in The Hole range from level forty to level sixty!)<br><br>Probably the best thing for you to do, is to follow <a href=HTTP://www.eqatlas.com/paineel.html target=_new><b>this link</b></a> and have a look at a map of Paineel.  This should allow you to get an idea of where you are <b>and</b> where you want to go.  You should be able to hunt in the Paineel newbie area for a few levels and then venture out into Toxxulia forest.<br><br>You could also try shouting in the zone, for someone to guide you to the newbie area, or another place, that you need to go.<br><br>If, my deductions were not entirely accurate and this was not what you were asking, it might be worth coming back and making your request for information crystal clear.  Then you will no doubt be deluged by insights and opinions, into what you need.<br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
