<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101257530039808></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101257530039808><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=101257530039808>RE: newbie necro</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=101257530039808#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=49677><span id=Guru>alaaraaf the Puissant</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>149 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Feb 1st 10:57 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey.<br><br><LI><i><b>1.gnome or darkelf</b></i><br>Am I qualified to answer this one?&nbsp;&nbsp;(I play an Iksar necromancer.  Does this disqualify my opinion?  Nah, just means it's not useful!  *Cackle*)<br>Frankly, I don't think the race thing is gonna make all that much difference to you.  If you want to explore, a gnome is probably better.  (You'll only start off KoS in Cabilis, as I understand it.)  Dark Elves have infravision, which is nice.  The difference in INT is negligable.<br>The only thing that'd effect me, if making this choice, is that Dark Elf necromancers are everywhere.  (I enjoy being different.)<br><br><LI><i><b>2.when do you get pet </b></i><br>You can buy your first pet at level one.  It's called <span style='color: red;'><b>Cavorting Bones</b></span style='color: red;'>.  It'll cost you a couple of gold, but a necromancer without a pet is very often a necromancer about to be beaten to a pulp.<br><a href=HTTP://www.eqclasses.com/ target=_new>EQNecro</a> have a <b>vast</b> amount of information about playing a necromancer.  You read their pet guide <b><a href=HTTP://necro.eqclasses.com/pets.asp target=_new>here</a></b>.  This will tell you what each pet is and what it's capabilities are.<br>A properly managed necromancer pet is a thing of awesome destructive powers!<br><br><LI><b><i>3.what is good equipment</b></i><br>That's kinda interpretational!<br>Good equipment is the very best thing you can get your hands on!  *Grin*  On a slightly less tangential approach...<br>Necromancers are INT casters.  So, the higher your INT, the more mana you get.  However, the amount of mana you get is based on a formula something like this:<br><span style='color: orange;'>Mana</span style='color: orange;'> = <span style='color: green;'>INT</span style='color: green;'> x (<span style='color: red;'>Level</span style='color: red;'> / <span style='color: blue;'>5</span style='color: blue;'>)<br>So, at lower levels, you get very little mana for each article of INT.  It is therefore useful to invest in +mana items.  (+HP items don't hurt either!  *Grin*)<br>A good, <i>fast</i> weapon is useful at lower levels too.  You can pick up a fast piercer for very little.<br><br><LI><i><b>4.what type of pet do they get</b></i><br>Go read the pet guide at EQNecro.  It literally tells you <b>everything</b> you could want to know.  Follow the link <a href=HTTP://necro.eqclasses.com/pets.asp target=_new><b>here</b></a>.<br><br>Well, that covers your questions.  Remember, you can always come back here and ask, if you have any more.  <br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
