<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101193936724746></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101193936724746><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=101193936724746>Some Answers</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=101193936724746#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=139029><span id= >Yorak</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jan 25th 2:17 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Level 56 necromancer with a few answers...<br><br>&quot;What's the best Race?&quot;<br><br>Not humans.&nbsp;&nbsp;Humans suck.  Low int, no nightvision, no real benefits...don't be one of these.<br><br>I'm not too keen on the Iksar, either, for three reasons.<br><br>First is the starting int, which is the same as humans (i.e. too low).<br><br>Second is the xp penalty.  20% more xp to level sucks.<br><br>Third, and most important, is the skeleton pets and lich form.  They have HUMAN skeleton pets and a HUMAN bone form!  This annoys me to no end.<br><br>Iksar do have a very big plus with their natural regen, though.  See, regen is a necromancer's friend, since we suck our life away turning it into mana.  Regen helps quite a bit.<br><br>So, I'd say be either a Dark Elf, a Gnome, or an Erudite.  Doesn't really matter which you pick, as all three of these are quite easy to get to 200+ int.  Pick whichever you like best.<br><br>&quot;What should I put my starting points into?&quot;<br><br>Easy.  Put as many as you can into intellegence and the rest into strength.  Intelligence is your most important attribute as an int caster, as your mana is based off of it.  Strength will help your weak caster ass from becoming encumbered so easily.<br><br>Alternately, you could put your leftover points into stamina, for a few extra hit points to convert into mana.  Dunno how much hp you'll get from those 5 leftover points, though...<br><br>&quot;What weapon skill do I need?&quot;<br><br>You don't.  Necromancers can use piercing as well as 1h and 2h blunt, but none of these are really important.  By the time you hit level 16, you won't be meleeing anymore.<br><br>For those first 16 levels though, I kind of preferred 1hb.  Of course, I was a poor, untwinked n00b who couldn't afford those spiffy int caster daggers, so you might want to try piercing.  Like I said, though, it really doesn't matter.<br><br>&quot;What's the necro epic?&quot;<br><br>Our epic is called the Scythe of the Shadowed Soul (aka Waterfoul of the Damned).  It's a stork's head on a stick that quacks at you and casts a spell we get anyway, but takes longer to do so.  To get it you need ultra-rare items from Fear, Hate, and Air.  My suggestion is not to bother.  Get a Zlandicar's Heart instead.<br><br>As for links, sorry, I don't have any.<br>&nbsp;<br>I'm not even here</td></tr>
