	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi again.<br><br>I have come across another couple of possibilities, for your expedient demise.&nbsp;&nbsp;These are both level fifty-nine spells.<br><br><LI><b>Trucidation:</b><br>This is a 1,100 point DD lifetap.  It wouldn't account for all your life, but it'd come damned close.  Having said this, it requires an essence emerald to cast and would be really wasted, in a duel.  (At least, unless that duel was a Best of the Best, or something significant!)<br><br><LI><b>Funeral Pyre:</b><br>This one isn't a DD spell, but it's <b>really</b> nasty!  Will do 2160 Damage over a 54 second period.  If you have fifteen hundred HP's, this would kill you in a fraction over forty seconds.  Or, this followed immediately by Trucidation, would burn you down real quickly.<br><br>Having said this, my suggestions thus far require that the necromancer you duelled was level fifty-nine.  And frankly, if you duelled a level fifty-nine necromancer, you should have expected something really awful to happen!  *Grin*<br><br>Anyhow, I'm outta suggestions for now.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br> <br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
