	   <tr><td colspan=2> Some of you may not agree with this but, I think it makes good sense.&nbsp;&nbsp;What is one of the reasons necros are not good in groups?  Well since most of our spells are time based, it makes us hard to live up to our potential in groups.  A good thing to do for a necro is have sow, or jboots and let the necro pull.  Pull with a good dot.  By the time you get back to group and everyone starts attacking the mob your spell may have time to live up to its damaging length.   Some say that dots make aggro too hard to get rid of.  Well i have tried this and unless your group has no taunters, or good melees then you will be fine.  This is just another way to use necros..  My 2cp anyway<br>&nbsp;<br>Sphoenix Darkfever</td></tr>
