	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey.<br><br>I'll ignore the areas Cannis has already covered.&nbsp;&nbsp;He made his point perfectly well and I think he made his point.  There are a few other things, however, that I will comment on, from the point of view of an Iksar necromancer.  (Currently a little over a quarter of the way through L45):<br><br><LI><i>i kill a mob, when im done i have about 60-70m i cob till fm then regen.</i><br>Personally, I try to finish up at full health.  I use Steelskin <b>all</b> the time and if I need to, I usually drain health back with Vampric Curse.<br>The reason for this, is that I use Allure of Death, while meditating.  My innate regeneration covers the drain of Allure and it's like a couple of points of free downtime mana regeneration, per tick.  Obviously, if I'm wounded, I don't heal, with Allure on.<br><br><LI><i>...you know that vc does not hurt the mob, as it does the damage over time...</i><br>Erm, what are you talking about here?  The mob takes damage as you are healed.  Go drop a Vampiric Curse on a decaying skeleton.  If it doesn't take damage, what killed it???  Admittedly, it's not a very efficient way to inflict damage, but that's not what it's for.  (Incidentally, you do know you get the full healing from the spell, even if your victim didn't have that much health, right?)<br><br><LI><i>...iksar may not get infravision, but they get night vision...</i><br>Actually, I think what we get <b>is</b> Infravision.  What Dark Elves have is Ultravision.  (I could be wrong, but I don't think so.  Anyhow, that's not really relevant.  Infravision, (asumin' that's what we have,) blows.  I haven't played one of the blind races yet, so maybe they're way, way worse, but I just wasn't impressed with Infravision at all.  Ultravision is far superior.  Admittedly, you get a spell for this at L24, but frankly, I'm <b>really</b> short of spell slots at the best of times.  I don't have the spare space for a vision spell.  (And I don't want to swap spells in and out.  I have to do that too much as it is!)<br><br><LI><i>If u want to level quickly (well faster than other necros) be an iksar.</i><br>We have an experience penalty for all the bonuses Iksar get.  I'm given to believe this is something like 20%!  I don't see how Iksar can level faster than other races, frankly.  The bonus we gain from our innate abilities is lessened with every level and the price for it never shrinks.  (A Dark Elf with same amount of experience as my Iksar necromancer should be about L47.  That's two levels higher, including the Hell level I'm mired in!!!)<br><span style='color: green;'>Do Iksar level faster than other races?  I honestly don't know.  I find it difficult to believe they do.</span style='color: green;'><br><br><LI><i>There is really no reason to make a de necro as far as i can see.</i><br>Dark Elves are a balance between Iksar and Erudites.  They don't have all our innate abilities, but they don't have a hideous experience penalty.  They don't have the huge mana pool, but they see in the dark and don't have foreheads like tower-shields!<br>It's far easier for a Dark Elf to gain faction with other cities, that for an Iksar.  (I read on another post a remark stating: <br><i>&quot;You're an Iksar.  With the faction they gave you, you're probably KoS to your own mother!&quot;</i><br>(I should've bookmarked it, but forgot.  But the comment is pretty accurate.)<br>Dark Elves can also wear their cultural chain armour, which makes them the only necromantic race that can wear heavy armour.  (To the best of my knowledge.)  Unlike Cabilis scale, (which we can't wear anyway,) this gives a nice INT bonus among other stats and a healthy boost to the armour-class.<br><br>There are very few very high level Iksar necromancers on the Torvonnilous server.  Is this not the case on your server also?  There has to be a reason for that, don't you think?<br><br>Beside which, wouldn't it be dull if there were only Iksar and Erudite necromancers?  Face it, female Dark Elves in robes are one of the best SoL models.  <i>(I'm a guy, I like the cleavage.  *Shrug*)</i>  <br><br>So, those are my thoughts.  I play an Iksar necromancer and personally, I love it.  <i>It drives me nuts when my EXP bar is refusing to move and my guild-mates are telling me how great their EXP gain is, but life's hard, innit?</i>  I really don't think the bonuses we get are as amazing as many people claim.  And as I said before, you pay a big price for them.  <i>(Cannis' Dark Elf necromancer should hit L60 with the same amount of experience that will see you and me half way through L58.  Yes, it's only a level and a half, but they're <span style='color: orange;'><b>really</b></span style='color: orange;'> big levels!}</i><br><br><br>Anyhow, that's it for now.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
